Ok, now it's extra useful:<p><pre><code>    paste () {
            (pbpaste | curl -s -F "sprunge=<-" http://sprunge.us | xargs echo -n && echo -n "?"$1) | pbcopy;
    }
</code></pre>
Usage: `paste <lang>`<p><pre><code>    fpaste () {
        (cat $1 | curl -s -F "sprunge=<-" http://sprunge.us | xargs echo -n && echo -n "?"$2) | pbcopy;
    }
</code></pre>
Usage: `fpaste <file> <lang>`<p>Pardon the lack of bash skills.
